subSubSection.paragraph:
Description
: Coloration (observed in the 
paratype
). General body color dark brown (
Fig. 108
). Lateral carinae of the frons above lateral ocelli and close to the median ocellus, vertex, lower region of the frons close to the median ocellus, gena, lora, maxillary lobe, median region of pronotum and mesonotum, epimeron and episternum yellow. Forewing: basal half dark brown and apical half light brown, with white regions: white rectangular spot before pterostigma; white diffuse band at the apex of the postcostal cell extending to the RA1 vein; narrow white stripe covering base of medial vein; white long stripe inside cell C2; white short stripe inside cell C3; white spot and wide in the apical half extending from the r-m cross-vein to the apex of clavus; wide, white, transverse band extending from the cell C3a’ to cell C3b; narrow white stripes covering Pcu and Pcu+A1 vein; narrow white stripe on the postclaval margin (
Fig. 133
). Pterostigma brown. Hindwing semi-hyaline, light brown. Legs dark brown, except mid coxa and hind coxa yellow, and hind femur light brown (
Fig. 108
). Upper half of sternite III, dorsal region of sternite IV and V yellow (
Figs 108, 112
).

Head: frons with median carina present, but weakly marked; lateral carina of frons strongly directed obliquely laterally (
Fig. 110
); vertex length subequal to the median length of the pronotum in dorsal view (
Fig. 111
); pedicel approximately 4 times longer than wide and scape inconspicuous (
Fig. 110
). Thorax: pronotum with median longitudinal carina present, but weakly marked; mesonotum with median and lateral longitudinal carinae present and strongly marked (
Fig. 111
). Forewing: m-cu cross-vein absent (
Fig. 133
). Legs: hind tibia with 6 apical spines; hind tarsus with 7+ 7 apical spines.

